    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HOUSTON \u2013\nThe Houston Baseball team dropped its Big 12 Conference opener to Kansas State, 20-8, in eight innings on Friday night at Don Sanders Field at Darryl and Lori Schroeder Park.\nJames Guyette (3-1) picked up the win for Kansas State (14-4, 1-0 Big 12), throwing 5.1 innings in which he allowed six runs on four hits and six walks. Senior\nChris Scinta\n(1-3) took the loss for Houston (11-6, 0-1 Big 12) after ceding four runs on four hits in 2.2 innings.\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nTre Broussard\n: 2-3, RBI, R, BB\nXavier Perez\n: 1-4, RBI, 2 R, SB\nJackson LaLima\n: 1-4, 3B, R\nNOTABLES\nSenior\nDylan Maxcey\ncaught two runners stealing.\nSophomore\nJackson LaLima\nhit his first career triple.\nHouston drew seven walks in the game.\nSenior\nCarsten Sabathia III\nhas reached base safely in 10 straight games.\nKEY INNINGS\n1\nst\n| Houston struck first. A single followed by four consecutive walks allowed redshirt sophomore\nXavier Perez\nand junior\nTre Broussard\nto score, putting the Cougars up 2-0.\n2\nnd\n| The Wildcats tied it in the top of the second. A double off the bat of Bear Madliak pushed two runs across to even the score.\nHouston reclaimed the lead in the bottom of the inning as sophomore\nMcClane Helton\nscored on a balk to take a 3-2 lead.\n5\nth\n| After Kansas State again tied the game in the third, the Wildcats took their first lead of the game with four runs in the fifth. With runners on first and second, Nick English hit a two-run double to center field to put the visitors up 5-3. Another run came across on a sacrifice fly while a fourth run scored on a single later in the inning to solidify Kansas State's lead.\n6\nth\n| The Wildcats added to their lead with a three-run homer in the top of the sixth, but Houston answered in the bottom of the inning. Two wild pitches after the Cougars loaded the bases allowed Maxcey and freshman\nBlake Fields\nto score, cutting the deficit to 10-5. A fielder's choice off the bat of Perez scored another while Broussard laced a single down the left-field line to plate a fourth, pushing the score to 10-7.\n8\nth\n| Following two runs in the seventh, Kansas State rallied for an eight-run inning in the eighth. Houston added a run to its tally in the bottom of the inning, but it was not enough to avoid the run-rule loss.\nUP NEXT\nHouston continues its series against Kansas State at 6:30 p.m. Saturday, before a 1 p.m. Sunday conclusion.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013"
